node.text: It’s a well known fact that winged eyeliner is notoriously hard to achieve, but make-up artist @RaoulAlejandre and @PoppyDelevingne are here to provide you with the insider tricks you need. In the latest #MakeUpMasters episode with #BritishVogue, watch as the pair take on the classic Hollywood look using the new make-up line from @Valentino.Beauty. You’ll be achieving winged eyeliner like #SophiaLoren in no time.

node.text: Amy Jackson has built her wardrobe around pre-loved pieces. Looking for clothes that give her the “feel-good factor”, the actor and model knows how to spot a glamorous vintage piece – including a dress previously owned by #PrincessMargaret. From celebrating renowned designers like @StellaMcCartney with an item that is “happiness in a jumper”, to championing new designers like @ClioPeppiatt, watch as Amy talks us through her seven favourite looks.

node.text: As the Olympic spirit sweeps the nation, let former Olympic gymnast Emilie Goldblum guide you through a restorative #WorkoutWednesday. From competing in the 2000 Summer Games in Sydney to performing with #Cher and #TheWeeknd, Emilie has done it all, so she’s no stranger to looking after her body to avoid injuries. Join in as she takes you through a 20 minute stretch session, and tag @BritishVogue in your next #WorkoutWednesday video to let us know where you're taking part.

Racing down LA’s Melrose Avenue in the California sun, supermodel #AlessandraAmbrosio takes on Vogue’s latest Shopping Challenge. The goal? She must style three animal-print outfits for three occasions, in just 60 minutes. Watch as she embraces her wild side as she styles a selection of looks for a brunch, job interview and party. 

This episode of The Shopping Challenge was filmed pre-pandemic and before social distancing guidelines were issued.

node.text: It’s a well-known fact that wearing SPF is one of the best ways to protect your skin – but how do you do it right to avoid signs of ageing and pigmentation? Watch as #BritishVogue’s beauty and lifestyle director @JessicaDiner does a sunscreen deep dive with @LaRochePosay dermatologist Dr Hiva Fassihi to discuss how to incorporate SPF into your everyday make-up routine (and why make-up with SPF isn’t enough), the difference between the effects of ultraviolet A and ultraviolet B on your skin, and why it’s important to apply sunscreen even if you’re not leaving the house.

node.title: Face Facts: The Importance Of SPF No Matter The Season

node.text: “You just can’t let fear get in the way.” That is @JourdanDunn’s biggest takeaway from her many years as a model, and her main piece of advice to others starting out. In #BritishVogue and @YouTube's fun and thought-provoking #VogueVisionaries masterclass, 31-year-old Dunn talks through the highs and lows of her time in the fashion industry, from early rejections to the headline-grabbing catwalk moments that defined her career. “Giving up is the easy option,” she says of the importance of taking risks. After all, “What’s the worst they can say?” Click the link in bio to watch the full video.

node.text: The wait is almost over. The final trailer for #TheEternals has dropped, and anticipation around the next @Marvel film is mounting. Starring #BritishVogue’s September cover star #GemmaChan, former cover star #AngelinaJolie, #SalmaHayek, and #RichardMadden – to name a few – the film is written and directed by ‘Nomadland’ director and Oscar-winner #ChloeZhao. Click the link in bio for everything you need to know about your next superhero obsession, and to watch the trailer in full.

node.text:
Health and happiness radiate from the beauty pages in the September 2021 issue of #BritishVogue. From optimism-inducing palettes and make-up with benefits, to the most delectable new-season scents and a conscious beauty special edited by @HannyCoates, the #BritishVogueBeauty team brings you how – and where – to find joy in the world of beauty. 

Read the beauty pages in full in the new issue, and click the link in bio for more from model of the moment, @_Yumi_Nu, as she talks about body positivity, confidence and the illusion of the “summer body”.

#YumiNu photographed by @RichardBurbridge, beauty director @JessicaDiner and styled by @DenaGia, with hair by @ShayAshual, make-up by @RaisaFlowers, nails by @JinSoonChoi and production by @Prodn_ArtAndCommerce.

node.text: Minimalists, look away now. For A-listers this summer, it’s a case of the more necklaces, the better. From #HaileyBieber and #Rihanna’s chains upon chains, to #DuaLipa and #EmilyRatajkowski’s beaded confections, click the link in bio for the #British Vogue guide on how to layer necklaces like the It-girls this summer.

node.text: When the Taliban began taking control of large swathes of Afghanistan in May, internally displaced persons began flooding into Kabul, only for the capital to fall in turn on 15 August.
